From 3c8f6fdc6e1d9c6e0a9d79b2c5f6b2ef8f4c9c57 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:15:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] thermal: mediatek: add MT6797 AUXADC support

The MT6797 thermal controller is compatible with the existing MediaTek
AUXADC-thermal architecture, but its bank topology, ADC calibration layout,
sampling parameters, and ADC-OE conversion differ from the variants currently
supported by the driver.

Add the recovered MT6797 data as a separate variant. Keep the board nodes
disabled until calibration ownership and runtime readings are validated.

The calibration cell is intentionally optional for now: the driver retains
the framework's safe default calibration behavior, while the Gemini DT does
not claim an efuse provider that has not yet been implemented.

Signed-off-by: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
